%H A383834 <a href="/index/Rec#order_05">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (5,-10,10,-5,1).
%F A383834 a(n) = 2*(A000217(n))^2 + 4*A000217(n) + 1.
%F A383834 a(n) = 6*A006007(n) + 1.
%F A383834 From _Andrew Howroyd_, Nov 12 2025: (Start)
%F A383834 a(n) = (n^4 + 2*n^3 + 5*n^2 + 4*n + 2)/2.
%F A383834 G.f.: (1 + 2*x + 6*x^2 + 2*x^3 + x^4)/(1 - x)^5. (End)
%e A383834 For n=1, the short leg is A002061(1) = 3 and the long leg is A212135(2) = 4 so the sum of the legs is then a(1) = 3 + 4 = 7.
%t A383834 a=Table[(n(n+1))/2,{n,0,40}];Apply[Join,Map[{2#^2+4#+1}&,a]]
